mentors.name: Joel Noble
mentors.description: Joel ("Mr.N") has been teaching at East High School since 2001 and has been a lead mentor and Head Coach for team 1339 since it was founded in 2003. He currently teaches Engineering, and works with the team leadership.

mentors.name: Chad Bartel
mentors.description: Chad works at ULA and has been with the team since 2011. He helps diagnose issues, troubleshoot, and advise both Programming and Electrical.

mentors.name: Arturo Earle
mentors.description: Arturo works in cyber security but has more fun mentoring the team on various tasks and helping our with infrastructure.

mentors.name: Jeff Kieft
mentors.description: Jeff is a biophysicist and professor. He is the treasurer and board member on the nonprofit, offers general team support, and helps manage scouting at competitions.

mentors.name: Garrett Calkins
mentors.description: Garrett is a manufacturing engineer for TriMas Life Sciences. He helps our team with manufacturing, strategy, and design. He has been with our team since 2022.

mentors.name: Critter Thompson
mentors.description: Critter is a programming mentor, who has spent many hours helping out wherever needed.

mentors.name: Craig Dorroh
mentors.description: Craig has driven our trailer to all 4 competitions in 2023, and has helped the team during each one of them.

mentors.name: Nathan Baldwin
mentors.description: Nathan Baldwin is a test engineer at Medtronic. This is his first year as a mentor so he has been helping the team where needed.

mentors.name: Nathaniel Chin
mentors.description: Nathaniel works as a CAD and design engineer at Lunasonde. He assists the team in CAD and design decisions.

mentors.name: Wes Naake
mentors.description: Wes is an alumn mentor from the class of '22. He helps with mechanical and manufacturing by assisting students while they build and maintain different parts on the robot.

mentors.name: Wren Bandrowski
mentors.description: Wren works for the Colorado Department of Transportation, and is a FIRST Alumni of team 4915. They started mentoring this season and help organize, motivate, and support the team.
